HEADWORD: Cabalistical
<hw>Cab`a*lis"tic*al</hw> <pr>(-t⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr> }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the cabala; containing or
conveying an occult meaning; mystic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Heptarchus is a <qex>cabalistic</qex> exposition of the first
chapter of Genesis</q>. <rj><qau>Hallam.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

